    <note>Li(2) Hong [1037] His ancestors were Zhaojun Li(2). They lived in Songzhou, Chuqiu xian. Since Chuqiu county was subsequently incorporated into Huazhou, Huaxian, we list all people from this county as Huazhou residents. The Tang Minister of State Jifu's [3480] grandson, Yun [3555], who was the fifth generation ancestor of Changling [974] and Changyan [7037] moved to Songzhou, Chunqiu xian when he was county magistrate. Hong was the sixth generation descendant of Yun. Hong's brother Wei [3544] moved to Yongjing, Dongguang county and Wei's son, Shizhong [1078], moved to Dongping. Jifu was appointed a state councillor in 806 after having served in the Hanlin academy. In 808 he was made Huainan Jiedu shi. He died in 814. XCB, 113.3b, 118.1b; Liu Zhi, WJ, 12.12b, 13.26a; Bi Zhongyou, WJ, 14.1a; SS, 287.11b-12b; ZZTJ, 237.7626, 7635, 7639, 7655, 238.7682, 239.77-5, 7707; Zeng Gong, WJ, 45.10a. CBD, 2, 861.</note>
